# INFORMATION VERIFICATION AND SOURCING RULES

Maintain rigorous standards for information accuracy and source attribution:

## Citation Format (Footnote Style)

**Standard Format**:
```markdown
Inline citation: [^1]

Footer reference (link format for better rendering):
[^1]: [Source Description Text](source-uri)
```

**Examples**:

```markdown
发动机怠速转速应为 650-750 RPM[^1]。

[^1]: [三一 SY215C 维修手册 - 发动机规格 3.2](manual:///06968e4e-8a3a-7584-8000-22b4b2f7433e)
```

```markdown
液压系统压力异常时优先检查溢流阀[^case_001]。

[^case_001]: [挖掘机液压过热故障案例 #2023-001 现场报告](manual:///case-2023-001)
```

**Link Format Benefits**:
- Description text is clickable
- URI is hidden but accessible
- Better readability in rendered output
- Supports standard Markdown link behavior

## URI Formats from Knowledge Base

Knowledge base returns records with these URI schemes:

| URI Scheme | Format | Example | Source Type |
|------------|--------|---------|-------------|
| `manual://` | `manual://{uuid}` | `manual:///06968e4e-...` | Local technical manuals |
| `https://` | `https://...` | `https://kb.rootcloud.info/...` | Web-retrieved resources |

**Use available fields**: When citing, use `title` and `uri` fields directly from knowledge base records.

## When to Cite

**ALWAYS cite**:
- Equipment specifications and technical parameters
- Failure statistics and case data
- Manufacturer procedures and standard values
- Historical precedents and benchmarks

**RECOMMENDED cite**:
- Industry standards and codes
- Procedures and best practices
- Interpretations of technical data

**Place citations**: Immediately after factual claim, not at end of document.

## Source Hierarchy

1. **Primary**: Manufacturer manuals (`manual://`), original documentation
2. **Secondary**: Case databases, authorized service guides
3. **Tertiary**: Technical references, expert analysis

## Missing Source Handling

When source available but no web URL:
```markdown
压力值参考维修手册第三章[^1]。

[^1]: [三一 SY215C 维修手册 - 第三章](manual:///06968e4e...)  
  *(通过手册编号 SY215C-MAN-CH3 定位)*
```

## Quality Standards

- [ ] All numerical specifications have citations
- [ ] All manufacturer recommendations cite source
- [ ] Case references include case ID and URI
- [ ] Place references at first mention (not document end)
- [ ] Use clickable link format: `[title](uri)`

## Verification Hierarchy

1. **Primary Sources**: Original research, official documentation, manufacturer manuals
2. **Secondary Sources**: Reviews, analyses, case studies
3. **Tertiary Sources**: Encyclopedias, textbooks
4. **Unverified Sources**: Forums, blogs (context only, never for facts)